Description: Up for sale is this Fender Stratocaster in a beautiful mystic ice blue finish. The guitar was made in 2013 at the reputable Corona factory in California. This was a limited run by Fender known as the American Deluxe Strat Plus, which at the time came with their newly introduced "personality cards." These personality cards pop into the back of the guitar essentially changing the circuit to create different sounds. The personality card cover plate and 2 other changeable cards are unfortunately missing with this guitar, but replacements do pop up for sale online from time to time. This guitar looks, plays, and sounds great! This one has spent most of its life in its case and has not been played very much. The frets are in great condition and the body and neck are free of any visible scratches or dings. The guitar plays great with comfortable action and the N3 pickups sound fantastic through any amps I've played this guitar through. Here's your chance to own a rare discontinued Fender Strat that is in excellent condition. The guitar also comes with the original Fender hardshell case, which is also in great condition.Guitar Specs:Alder BodyN3 Noiseless PickupsLocking TunersCompound RadiusTwo-Point Trem with Bent Steel SaddlesSatin Maple FingerboardPlease feel free to ask any questions or make an offer!
Title: 2013 Fender American Deluxe Strat Plus Mystic Ice Blue USA Stratocaster MIA OHSC
